data.title: Sarpir, Kurdistan
data.meta_description: Sarpir is a village in Uraman Takht Rural District, Uraman District, Sarvabad County, Kurdistan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 727, in 171 families. The village is populated by Kurds.
data.text:
Sarpir (Persian: سرپير, also Romanized as Sarpīr)[1] is a village in Uraman Takht Rural District, Uraman District, Sarvabad County, Kurdistan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 727, in 171 families.[2] The village is populated by Kurds.[3]
